      "writtenOn": "2020-04-10T19:54:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are they redacted via dalddr as well?\n\nThis is probably a bad idea, but I’ll say it anyways: Because this runs in-process, the sinkhole function detector be based off address ranges instead. The start address is fairly easy to find given dladdr for C functions or class_getMethodImplementation for ObjC. Then you need to know where the function’s text ends to create a testable range, which is a bit of a harder problem. One option is nlist, but I don’t know if that works on iOS. Another option would be to bisect (or linear scan) with dladdr() to figure out when a new function starts. This won’t be perfect though because an unexported function between two exported ones will attribute incorrectly.",
      "parentUuid": "4845f62b_a0822e60",
